#eNCA Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Eskom announced that Stage 4 blackouts will continue until Wednesday. The power utility says this is due to unlawful industrial action at various Eskom power stations that has impacted planned maintenance and repairs. READ: Farmers appealing with Eskom It counts unlawful labour action, which is messing with scheduled maintenance and a fault line. This action has prevented South Africa from adding a further 600-MegaWatts due to a line fault in Mozambique. Watch the video above for more details on this story. #POWERALERT1
Unlawful industrial action at various Eskom power stations has impacted planned maintenance and repairs, and at some stations the full complement of workers have not reported for duty. As
a result, Stage 4 loadshedding will regretfully continue to be implemented pic.twitter.com/6iN4wRi8Al